{"id":"wagon","term":"Wagon","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Heb. aghalah; so rendered in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 45:19\">Gen. 45:19</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 45:21\">21</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:27\">27</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 46:5\">46:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 7:3\">Num. 7:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 7:7\">7</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 7:8\">8</a>, but elsewhere rendered “cart” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 6:7\">1 Sam. 6:7</a>, etc.). This vehicle was used for peaceful purposes. In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 23:24\">Ezek. 23:24</a>, however, it is the rendering of a different Hebrew word, and denotes a war-chariot.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 45:19","Genesis 45:21","Genesis 1:27","Genesis 46:5","Numbers 7:3","Numbers 7:7","Numbers 7:8","1 Samuel 6:7","Ezekiel 23:24"]}